task.summary: Re-organised the code structure Changed BufferedWriter to a more functional design Re-factored Gibbs updates to be more Scala-idiomatic Fixed a bug in the updateBlocks function, which meant that the blockId wasn't being updated for the record-type rows.

- Redesigned the BufferedWriter: now stores RDDs in a buffer then applies a sc.union operation when flushing. - Fixed bug in updateSummaryVariables function: distortion contribution was being erroneously calculated for each row, rather than each partition. - Fixed bug in `read` method for DriverState which was causing an exception when deserializing saved state. - Added `save` method for Diagnostics -

- Added functionality for validation/evaluation - Re-factored MCMC diagnostics functionality - Modified the updateSummaryVariables function so that it uses local accumulators to compute the within-partition likelihood (before the "global" accumulator values were being used, which may not have been accurate within the partition) - Changed the interface for Accumulators so that they better conform to the Spark AccumulatorV2 specification
Renamed package to sparkeber Added LICENSE
- Refactored the State object (better variable names) - Moved functionality for saving the local variables on the driver into the State class (previously this was in a DriverState class)

MESSAGE.value: - Redesigned the BufferedWriter: now stores RDDs in a buffer then applies a sc.union operation when flushing. - Fixed bug in updateSummaryVariables function: distortion contribution was being erroneously calculated for each row, rather than each partition. - Fixed bug in `read` method for DriverState which was causing an exception when deserializing saved state. - Added `save` method for Diagnostics -

- Added functionality for validation/evaluation - Re-factored MCMC diagnostics functionality - Modified the updateSummaryVariables function so that it uses local accumulators to compute the within-partition likelihood (before the "global" accumulator values were being used, which may not have been accurate within the partition) - Changed the interface for Accumulators so that they better conform to the Spark AccumulatorV2 specification
Renamed package to sparkeber Added LICENSE
- Refactored the State object (better variable names) - Moved functionality for saving the local variables on the driver into the State class (previously this was in a DriverState class)
- Combined State and InitialState objects
Huge commit
Removed use of ArrayBuilders, since they're inefficient when the size is unknown.
Changed Array.fill(size) to Array.ofDim(size) where possible.
Renamed package to "spark-eber"
Remove first-names.txt
Added copyright headers to new files.

Added support for generic partition function (not only k-d tree) Changed to ClassTag/Ordering type class rather than implicit Saved linkage structure now includes the isolated entities Changed saved summary statistics from numIsolatedEntities to numObservedEntities
More fixes in changing from numIsolates to numObservedEntities Prefer `recIds` as a variable name over `cluster` BufferedWriter class now supports generic types

Added logging with log4j Changed representation of numDistortions in the output (to a single map, rather than a map of maps) Added input validity checks for Parameters Allow specification of string index parameters through Parameters
Fixed log layout
Fix KDTreePartitioner behaviour when doing no splits Save initial state to disk when not doing burn-in Add kCluster diagnostic function
kClust function renamed and output CSV file includes header row

Renamed "validation" package to "analysis" Using implicit function defs rather than creating specialised RDDs for Clusters, PairwiseLinks, etc. Added a FileWriter (for use on the driver node) Renamed BufferedWriter to BufferedRDDWriter Added a class specifically for writing the diagnostics to a csv Changed representation of NumDistortions and DistProbs types (to use Fields object) Renamed "partitions.parquet" to "partitionsState.parquet" Changed PartitionState to LinkageState (since it no longer contains the diagnostics)
Added LinkageStructureWriter
Moved `nextState` function from Sampler class to State class

- Print performance metrics to log - Increase threshold for set domain splitter from 5 to 30 - Decrease buffer size for file writer to 4KB - Add implementation for building similar string index based on VP trees - Add SHIW dataset

- Added new summary variable: frequency distribution over the number of distortions per record - Renamed numDistortions to aggDistortions - Changed steepness parameter (in distribution over string field) to a temperature parameter

- Re-factor experiments using a generic class called EBER - Change "linkageStructure.parquet" -> "linkageChain.parquet" - Overwrite by default when saving clusters - Add code for collapsing over the distortions when updating the links - Use RDD rather than Dataset in a few places
Add function for saving partition sizes along the chain
Compute most probable clusters in the evaluation function
